{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017wnLdDaQmwZ9y8xH6oDejj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Issue #983: Create `.data.frame` methods for `as_forecast<type>`\n     2→\n     3→## Source\n     4→\n     5→- **GitHub**: https://github.com/epiforecasts/scoringutils/issues/983\n     6→- **Action Summary**: Rename the 7 existing `.default` methods to `.data.frame` (since they assume data.frame-like input), then create new `.default` methods that error with a helpful message about unsupported types. Update NAMESPACE, docs, and tests.\n     7→- **Status Note**: Still relevant. Prerequisite #981 (making `as_forecast_*` S3 generics) is done. Currently all 7 types only have `.default` methods; no `.data.frame` methods exist. The `.default` methods silently accept any type and rely on `as.data.table()` coercion deep inside.\n     8→\n     9→## Test Specifications\n    10→\n    11→**Designed**: 2026-02-13\n    12→**Test file**: `tests/testthat/test-class-forecast.R` (existing) and individual `test-class-forecast-*.R` files (existing)\n    13→**Testing patterns observed**: testthat with data.table fixtures; `example_*` datasets from package; `suppressMessages()` wrappers around `as_forecast_*()` calls; `expect_error()`, `expect_no_condition()`, `expect_identical()` used extensively; `setup.R` pre-computes score objects.\n    14→\n    15→### Important S3 dispatch note\n    16→\n    17→`data.table` has class `c(\"data.table\", \"data.frame\")` and tibble has class `c(\"tbl_df\", \"tbl\", \"data.frame\")`. When `.default` is renamed to `.data.frame`, R's S3 dispatch will still route data.table and tibble inputs to the `.data.frame` method because both inherit from `data.frame`. The new `.default` will only fire for types that do NOT inherit from `data.frame`.\n    18→\n    19→---\n    20→\n    21→### Test 1: test_that(\"as_forecast_binary.data.frame works with a plain data.frame\", { ... })\n    22→\n    23→**Reproduces**: Confirms that the renamed `.data.frame` method works with plain data.frame input (same behavior as the old `.default` method).\n    24→**File**: `tests/testthat/test-class-forecast-binary.R`\n    25→**Setup**:\n    26→- Create a plain `data.frame` from `example_binary`: `df <- as.data.frame(na.omit(example_binary))`\n    27→**Action**:\n    28→- Call `as_forecast_binary(df)`\n    29→**Expected**:\n    30→- `expect_no_condition(as_forecast_binary(df))` — no errors or warnings\n    31→- `expect_s3_class(result, \"forecast_binary\")` — returns proper class\n    32→- The result should be scoreable: `expect_no_error(score(result))`\n    33→**Fails now because**:\n    34→- This test should PASS with current code (`.default` handles it) and continue to PASS after the fix. It's a regression guard.\n    35→\n    36→### Test 2: test_that(\"as_forecast_quantile.data.frame works with a plain data.frame\", { ... })\n    37→\n    38→**Reproduces**: Confirms `.data.frame` method works for quantile forecasts with a data.frame (partially tested already at line 92-94 of test-class-forecast-quantile.R, but this is more thorough).\n    39→**File**: `tests/testthat/test-class-forecast-quantile.R`\n    40→**Setup**:\n    41→- Use `example_quantile_df` (already defined in `setup.R` as `as.data.frame(na.omit(example_quantile))`)\n    42→**Action**:\n    43→- Call `as_forecast_quantile(example_quantile_df)`\n    44→**Expected**:\n    45→- `expect_no_condition(as_forecast_quantile(example_quantile_df))`\n    46→- `expect_s3_class(result, \"forecast_quantile\")`\n    47→**Fails now because**:\n    48→- This test should PASS both before and after. It's a regression guard confirming the existing data.frame test (line 93) keeps working.\n    49→\n    50→### Test 3: test_that(\"as_forecast_sample.data.frame works with a plain data.frame\", { ... })\n    51→\n    52→**Reproduces**: Verifies sample forecast creation from a plain data.frame.\n    53→**File**: `tests/testthat/test-class-forecast-sample.R`\n    54→**Setup**:\n    55→- `df <- as.data.frame(na.omit(example_sample_continuous))`\n    56→**Action**:\n    57→- Call `as_forecast_sample(df)`\n    58→**Expected**:\n    59→- `expect_no_condition(as_forecast_sample(df))`\n    60→- `expect_s3_class(result, \"forecast_sample\")`\n    61→- `expect_no_error(score(result))`\n    62→**Fails now because**:\n    63→- Should PASS both before and after. Regression guard.\n    64→\n    65→### Test 4: test_that(\"as_forecast_point.data.frame works with a plain data.frame\", { ... })\n    66→\n    67→**Reproduces**: Verifies point forecast creation from a plain data.frame.\n    68→**File**: `tests/testthat/test-class-forecast-point.R`\n    69→**Setup**:\n    70→- `df <- as.data.frame(na.omit(example_point))`\n    71→**Action**:\n    72→- Call `as_forecast_point(df)`\n    73→**Expected**:\n    74→- `expect_no_condition(as_forecast_point(df))`\n    75→- `expect_s3_class(result, \"forecast_point\")`\n    76→**Fails now because**:\n    77→- Should PASS both before and after. Regression guard.\n    78→\n    79→### Test 5: test_that(\"as_forecast_nominal.data.frame works with a plain data.frame\", { ... })\n    80→\n    81→**Reproduces**: Verifies nominal forecast creation from a plain data.frame.\n    82→**File**: `tests/testthat/test-class-forecast-nominal.R`\n    83→**Setup**:\n    84→- `df <- as.data.frame(na.omit(example_nominal))`\n    85→**Action**:\n    86→- Call `as_forecast_nominal(df)`\n    87→**Expected**:\n    88→- `expect_no_condition(as_forecast_nominal(df))`\n    89→- `expect_s3_class(result, \"forecast_nominal\")`\n    90→**Fails now because**:\n    91→- Should PASS both before and after. Regression guard.\n    92→\n    93→### Test 6: test_that(\"as_forecast_ordinal.data.frame works with a plain data.frame\", { ... })\n    94→\n    95→**Reproduces**: Verifies ordinal forecast creation from a plain data.frame.\n    96→**File**: `tests/testthat/test-class-forecast-ordinal.R`\n    97→**Setup**:\n    98→- `df <- as.data.frame